Quack Quack 11/19/2024 11:29 PM
I think this org, fundamentally, was a huge success. I would like to thank production, especially, Fish and Jenna, for making their dream a reality. Thank you to the spectators and other players for making this an unforgettable experience. With that being said, speaking personally, this game had an incredibly negative impact on my mental health (which is partially my fault hahaha). I lost sleep, I lost sanity, and I lost three pounds. While some may have differing opinions on what's "fair" or "ok" in games, and the phrase "it's just a game" absolutely exists, I do believe some of the groupthink went too far. I have used the word bullying before, and while it may not be that extreme, I do think there is a warranted discussion there. I was complicit in this as well, I am no angel. If anyone, player, spectator, or production, wants to talk about it ever, my dms are open. I hold no ill will toward anybody I played with, but I understand that some might have been hurt by my actions. On the more positive side, I am incredibly grateful for the friends I made this season. I hope those are relationships that will last me a lifetime. Thank you for having me Snackvivor.
